# Slash Commands

When the user types any of these commands (with or without the slash), execute the corresponding workflow.

## /run

Launch the app locally for testing:

```bash
cd /Users/jacobvanalmelo/code/ffmpeg_app
PYTHONPATH=src python -m ffmpeg_app.main
```

## /test

Run the test suite:

```bash
cd /Users/jacobvanalmelo/code/ffmpeg_app
PYTHONPATH=src python -m pytest tests/ -v
```

## /build

Clean build the macOS .app bundle:

```bash
cd /Users/jacobvanalmelo/code/ffmpeg_app
rm -rf dist/ build/
pyinstaller --clean -y pyinstaller-macos.spec
```

## /sign

Code-sign the built app (requires build first). Read `signing-config.local.sh` for the identity:

```bash
source signing-config.local.sh
cd dist
codesign --deep --force --options runtime \
  --entitlements ../entitlements.plist \
  --sign "$CODESIGN_IDENTITY" \
  FFmpegWrapper.app
codesign --verify --deep --strict FFmpegWrapper.app
```

## /notarize

Zip, submit for notarization, staple, and verify (requires sign first). Read `signing-config.local.sh` for the profile:

```bash
source signing-config.local.sh
cd dist
rm -f FFmpegWrapper.zip
ditto -c -k --keepParent FFmpegWrapper.app FFmpegWrapper.zip
xcrun notarytool submit FFmpegWrapper.zip --keychain-profile "$NOTARIZE_PROFILE" --wait
xcrun stapler staple FFmpegWrapper.app
spctl -a -vv FFmpegWrapper.app
```

## /release

Full pipeline: build + sign + notarize + re-zip for distribution. Run /build, then /sign, then /notarize, then re-zip:

```bash
cd /Users/jacobvanalmelo/code/ffmpeg_app/dist
rm -f FFmpegWrapper.zip
ditto -c -k --keepParent FFmpegWrapper.app FFmpegWrapper.zip
```

## /deps

Install all dependencies:

```bash
cd /Users/jacobvanalmelo/code/ffmpeg_app
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```
